radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is dilated up to 1.0 cm, with a thickened hyper enhancing wall, and mild surrounding fat stranding. Visualized lung fields are within normal limits. There is no evidence of pleural or pericardial effusion. The liver, pancreas, spleen, adrenal glands, kidneys, stomach, small bowel loops, colon, rectum, bladder, uterus, bilateral adnexa, and soft tissues are unremarkable. There is no lymphadenopathy or evidence of osseous lesions or acute fracture.
